# CODEOWNERS Example File
# This file demonstrates the syntax supported by the CODEOWNERS extension

# Default owners for everything in the repo
* @global-owner @org/global-team

# Documentation
*.md @docs-team @tech-writers
/docs/ @documentation

# Frontend
*.js @frontend-team
*.jsx @frontend-team
*.ts @typescript-team
*.tsx @typescript-team
/src/components/ @ui-team

# Backend
*.go @backend-team
*.rs @rust-team
/api/ @backend-team @api-maintainers

# DevOps and Infrastructure
Dockerfile @devops
docker-compose.yml @devops @infrastructure
*.tf @terraform-team
/.github/ @github-admins
/.github/workflows/ @ci-cd-team

# Database
/migrations/ @database-team
*.sql @database-team

# Configuration files
*.yml @config-owners
*.yaml @config-owners
*.toml @config-owners
*.json @config-owners

# Section with approvers
[Critical Files]
/src/core/ @core-maintainers @security-team
/src/auth/ @security-team

[Infrastructure] @sre-team @platform-team
*.tf @terraform-experts
k8s/ @kubernetes-team

# Wildcard patterns
**/*.test.js @testing-team
**/test/ @qa-team

# Email addresses (less common but supported)
/legal/ legal@company.com
/compliance/ compliance@company.com

# Multiple owners
/important/ @owner1 @owner2 @org/team1 @org/team2

# Nested paths
/src/features/auth/**/*.go @auth-team @security-team
/src/features/payments/**/*.go @payments-team @finance-team
